WEBVTT



00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.160
Hi, I'm Kathy Keller. Each year when we get to Thanksgiving, we pause to recognize all the ways God has been so gracious

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:09.760
In his provision.

00:00:09.472 --> 00:00:12.096
Both for our basic physical needs

00:00:11.968 --> 00:00:16.736
And for the ways that he provides for us spiritually to give us joy

00:00:16.608 --> 00:00:20.160
hope and renewal through his son Jesus Christ.

00:00:20.576 --> 00:00:27.264
Thanksgiving has the potential to become rote or generic if we don't put our focus on God and his goodness.

00:00:27.104 --> 00:00:37.152
I want to encourage you to use the day as an opportunity to meditate on his word and the direction it gives us to see God and all he is, our strength and our strength.

00:00:36.672 --> 00:00:38.240
Strength and shield.

00:00:37.888 --> 00:00:39.360
Helper

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:44.768
our refuge, our savior and friend. And I know I'm going to be just as much as

00:00:44.576 --> 00:00:54.624
You are up to my ears and stuffing and mashed potatoes and guests and everything, but just go lock yourself in the bathroom for five minutes for heaven's sakes and be thankful.

00:00:54.144 --> 00:00:54.752
Oh.

00:00:54.784 --> 00:00:55.968
Or something.

00:00:56.576 --> 00:01:00.896
Listen to these words from Psalm 28, verses 6 and 7.

00:01:01.184 --> 00:01:02.944
Blessed be the Lord.

00:01:02.752 --> 00:01:06.400
For he has heard the voice of my pleas for mercy.

00:01:06.336 --> 00:01:10.688
"The Lord is my strength and my shield. In Him my heart trusts."

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:13.536
And I am helped and my heart exalts.

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:16.608
And with my song, I give thanks to him.

00:01:16.896 --> 00:01:23.136
These verses are a powerful reminder of all we have because Jesus loved us so much.

00:01:23.008 --> 00:01:25.184
That he gave his life for us.

00:01:25.248 --> 00:01:29.600
I encourage you to think of all the ways God provides for you.

00:01:29.312 --> 00:01:34.528
And I trust that God's Spirit will generate joy, praise, and thanksgiving.

00:01:34.208 --> 00:01:37.664
It comes from focusing on his amazing love.

00:01:38.208 --> 00:01:45.728
Please join us as we give thanks for all God is doing and for all he's done through gospel and life this past year.

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:55.808
We're so grateful for the encouragement we get from the messages we receive, telling us how God is bringing people to trust God through you and through this ministry.

00:01:55.328 --> 00:01:56.352
Ministry.

00:01:56.256 --> 00:02:02.720
So it's not merely a throwaway kind of statement when I say we have so much to be thankful for this year.

00:02:02.528 --> 00:02:04.384
We really do.

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:11.616
Now I want to note just a few things our team here at Gospel and Life gives thanks for in 2025.

00:02:11.712 --> 00:02:18.240
For the more than 214,000 people who receive our quarterly journal and emails.

00:02:18.176 --> 00:02:22.624
for the millions of people who listen to our podcast around the world.

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:27.040
For the thousands of people who shared one of our resources with someone.

00:02:26.848 --> 00:02:36.896
And for the 284,000 downloads of the Questioning Christianity podcast by people exploring or sharing the gospel.

00:02:36.416 --> 00:02:37.248
Gospel.

00:02:36.992 --> 00:02:42.400
On behalf of everyone here at Gospel and Life, we also give thanks to God for you.

00:02:42.144 --> 00:02:47.104
For your prayers, your gifts, and how you're missionally sharing our content,

00:02:46.816 --> 00:02:48.608
With those in your life.

00:02:48.608 --> 00:02:53.088
Thank you for your partnership as together we endeavor to reach others

00:02:52.832 --> 00:02:55.584
with a message of Christ's love.

00:02:55.904 --> 00:02:59.616
thanks be to god he's changed everything through christ.

00:02:59.712 --> 00:03:02.080
Have a joyful Thanksgiving.
